OL,3,CMet Office explains why amber weather
OL,4,Cwarning wasn't issued for Storm Bert
OL,6,FThere are three categories of weather
OL,7,Fwarnings which the Met Office can
OL,8,Fissue: yellow, amber and red.
OL,10,FYellow and amber warnings represent a
OL,11,Frange of impact levels and
OL,12,Flikelihoods, with red being reserved
OL,13,Ffor the situations where people must
OL,14,Fact to stay safe.
OL,16,FAs of midday on Tuesday, 26 November,
OL,17,Fthe number of homes flooded across
OL,18,FWales stood at 433 - more than 100 of
OL,19,Fwhich are in Rhondda Cynon Taf alone.
OL,20,FMany of them were affected during
OL,21,FStorm Dennis in 2020.
