OL,3,CMet Office explains why amber weather
OL,4,Cwarning wasn't issued for Storm Bert
OL,6,F"Here at the Met Office, our job is to
OL,7,Fget that message out there to allow
OL,8,Fpeople to protect themselves. As we
OL,9,Fget closer to the event, we also work
OL,10,Fclosely with the local authorities,
OL,11,FWelsh Government, emergency services
OL,12,Fand Natural Resources Wales to make
OL,13,Fsure we are as prepared as possible.
OL,15,F"Our weather warnings are broad, in a
OL,16,Fsense, to cover large areas but then
OL,17,Fwe work locally with Natural Resources
OL,18,FWales in order to inform their flood
OL,19,Fwarning."
